args: Thank you for coming to see me today.
Now then, you wish for me to look into the\nfuture of yourself and the boy you are in\nlove with, correct?
Y-yes! Er, please? Um, I mean...
Heh. There's no need to be so nervous.\nLet me have a look...
Hmm... Oh my. I fear your road will not\nbe an easy one.
I knew it... There's no way he would fall for\nsomeone like me.
Oh, that's not what I'm saying at all.
Certainly, the way things stand now,\nthe chances of love blossoming between\nthe two of you are quite low.
But that just means you need to change\nthe way ＂things stand.＂
Um, okay? How do I do that, exactly?
First, take a deep breath. You need to take\neverything one step at a time and only do\nwhat you can.
O-okay? Geez, I hope I can do this...
Hey, Verica. I heard you wanted me for\nsomething?
Thank you for coming. I was hoping you\ncould do something to help this young\nlady, actually.
Stop! You're never going to change\nanything if you just keep running away.
...In other words, even the simple\nact of looking a man in the eyes\nmakes her nervous.
I see. So that's why you called me here.
I'm sorry to burden you with something\nlike this.
I-i-i-it's...nice to...m-meet you?\nI mean...yes? Yes! Wait... Eeep.
Are you all right? Stay with us!
You came to see Verica again, huh?
You seem much more confident than when\nI first met you.
Y-you really think so?\nI'm happy to hear that.
Now you see what I meant when I said\nthat simply altering your outlook can\nchange a person completely.
I do. Thank you very much.
In fact, I think I'm going to try confessing\nmy love to him now!
I hope it goes well for you.
Thank you. I'll give it my best.
I suppose I am. I've been helping her every\nday of late, and I think the strain is\nstarting to get to me.
Heh. She has been around you a lot lately.
This isn't really what I should be doing,\nthough.
I had no idea that seers helped\nand advised people like this.
I always figured they would just tell people\ntheir fortune and that was it.
Ordinarily, that IS how it works.
But I want to do as much as I can to help\nthe people whose fortunes I tell.
The reason that people rely on seers is\nbecause they want to change something\nabout how they are.

So I feel our role is not to simply provide
them with an immutable future, but to give
them hope that future can be changed—
that THEY can change.

That makes sense. And while I have no
idea how her confession will go, I think
you've given her plenty of room to believe
she can change how she is.
H-he said there's already someone he's in\nlove with...
That's a shame. I was hoping it would be\npossible to change the sad future that\nawaited you.
But please do not let yourself become too\ndisheartened. I'm sure that someone who\nwill love you for who you are will come—
Oh, don't worry about me. I'm sad to have\nbeen turned down, but I'm not THAT sad.
My hopes of a relationship might have\nbeen dashed, but you've showed me that\neven someone like me can change.
Before, I felt like if he turned me down my\nentire world would have collapsed,\nbut now I'm much more positive.
If anything, I feel like I want to hurry up\nand fall in love with someone else.
And I owe all of that to you!
Y-you're awfully close to me...\nC-can you move away a little...?
But I wanna be with you foreeeever!
